This project allows a user to create a Centos VM for pre-Europa Zenoss
source-build development.  The intended usage is to check out source code on
the host, perform a source build on the guest, mount the host's source on the
guest, and link to the mounted source.  Then code can be edited/built on the
host and changes will be reflected on running code on the guest.  

Bring up the VM
---------------

    $ mkdir zenoss
    $ mkdir impact
    $ vagrant up

Build on the guest:
-------------------

    $ vagrant ssh
    $ sudo su - zenoss
    $ mkdir build; cd build
    $ svn co http://dev.zenoss.com/svnint/branches/core/zenoss-4.x/inst

Then perform normal configure, build, mkzenossinstance steps

Checkout on the host:
---------------------
The Vagrantfile will mount ./zenoss as /home/zenoss/work and ./impact as 
/home/zenossimpact/work

    $ cd ./zenoss
    $ svn checkout http://dev.zenoss.com/svnint/branches/core/zenoss-4.x/ core
    $ git clone https://github.com/zenoss/ZenPacks.zenoss.Impact.git

    $ cd ./impact
    $ git clone https://github.com/zenoss/impact-server.git

Link to the built files:
-----------------------

    $ vagrant ssh
    $ sudo su - zenoss
    $ ln -s /home/zenoss/work/core/Products /opt/zenoss/Products

    $ sudo su - zenossimpact
    $ ln -s /home/zenossimpact/work/impact-server/target/zenoss-dsa-4.2.5.70.0-SNAPSHOT /opt/zenoss_impact/webapps/zenoss-dsa.war
